A health worker sprays disinfectant commuters hands to combat the spread of coronavirus disease (COVID-19). JOHANNESBURG - Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu says 41 000 water tanks have been secured for more than 2 000 communities that need them. The National Command Council updated the nation on the lockdown on Saturday afternoon. COVID-19 in SA: Cases rise to 1170 "We have gone ahead with procuring water tanks and we have procured 41 000 of them and the greatest number is the one that goes to the Eastern Cape", said Sisulu. The number of confirmed coronavirus cases in South Africa is 1170. The virus has killed one person in the Western Cape. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.